                                                                                               NIST SP 800-161r1                                   CYBERSECURITY SUPPLY CHAIN RISK MANAGEMENT
                                                                                                                                                      PRACTICES FOR SYSTEMS AND ORGANIZATIONS


                                                                                                Term                       Definition
                                                                                                threat scenario            A set of discrete threat events, associated with a specific threat
                                                                                                [NIST SP 800-30 Rev. 1]    source or multiple threat sources, partially ordered in time.


                                                                                                threat source              The intent and method targeted at the intentional exploitation
                                                                                                [NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5]    of a vulnerability or a situation and method that may
                                                                                                                           accidentally trigger a vulnerability.
                                                                                                transparency               See visibility.
This publication is available free of charge from: https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.SP.800-161r1




                                                                                                trust                      The confidence one element has in another, that the second
                                                                                                [SwA]                      element will behave as expected.


                                                                                                trustworthiness            The interdependent combination of attributes of a person,
                                                                                                [NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5,    system, or enterprise that provides confidence to others of the
                                                                                                adapted]                   qualifications, capabilities, and reliability of that entity to
                                                                                                                           perform specific tasks and fulfill assigned responsibilities. The
                                                                                                                           degree to which a system (including the technology
                                                                                                                           components that are used to build the system) can be expected
                                                                                                                           to preserve the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of the
                                                                                                                           information being processed, stored, or transmitted by the
                                                                                                                           system across the full range of threats.
                                                                                                validation                 Confirmation, through the provision of objective evidence, that
                                                                                                [ISO 9000]                 the requirements for a specific intended use or application
                                                                                                                           have been fulfilled.

                                                                                                                           Note: The requirements were met.
                                                                                                verification               Confirmation, through the provision of objective evidence, that
                                                                                                [CNSSI 4009]               specified requirements have been fulfilled.
                                                                                                [ISO 9000, adapted]
                                                                                                                           Note: The intended output is correct.
                                                                                                visibility                 Amount of information that can be gathered about a supplier,
                                                                                                [ISO/IEC 27036, adapted]   product, or service and how far through the supply chain this
                                                                                                                           information can be obtained.
                                                                                                vulnerability              Weakness in an information system, system security
                                                                                                [NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5]    procedures, internal controls, or implementation that could be
                                                                                                                           exploited or triggered by a threat source.
                                                                                                vulnerability assessment   Systematic examination of a system or product or supply chain
                                                                                                [NIST SP 800-53 Rev. 5,    element to determine the adequacy of security measures,
                                                                                                adapted]                   identify security deficiencies, provide data from which to
                                                                                                                           predict the effectiveness of proposed security measures, and
                                                                                                                           confirm the adequacy of such measures after implementation.


